        "name": "image_to_video",
        "description": "Generate a video from a single source image and return the result so the model can continue with further actions. Provide `image` for the image to animate and optionally a `prompt` to guide the animation. Use this tool when the user provides an image and wants it animated, turned into a video, or used as the first frame. The source image may be a filesystem path, HTTPS URL, or `data:image/...;base64,...` URL. If `prompt` is omitted, a natural animation applies automatically. Duration can be 6 or 10 seconds; default to 6 unless the user requests longer. Resolution can be 480p or 720p; default to 480p unless the user specifically requests higher quality. Example: image_to_video(image=\"/Users/me/photo.jpg\", prompt=\"gentle camera push-in with wind moving the hair\", duration=6, resolution_name=\"480p\")",
